File: A self-proclaimed prophet spread misleading information, which breaches regulations. JOHANNESBURG - A self-described prophet has been arrested in Limpopo for spreading fake news about the lockdown. The man was nabbed in the Thohoyandou area. Police had received a tip-off from the public after a video circulated on social media. READ: Coronavirus In SA: Spreading fake news could land you in jail In the video, the man denounces the call to stay at home. The man also spread misleading information, which breaches regulations. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. 